cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and their application in computer vision problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for learning the structure and strength of filters in CNNs, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques for reducing the number of parameters required for training, which falls under the category of numerical optimization. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on various datasets, which involves data processing and analysis. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
